#  Simple Python Alarm Clock (Console-Based)

A simple Python script that works as an alarm clock by checking system time and triggering a beep sound when the set time is reached.

##  Features
- Set alarm using 24-hour format (HH:MM:SS)
- Continuously checks system time
- Plays beep sound when alarm triggers
- Simple and lightweight CLI application

##  Requirements
- Python 3.x
- Windows OS (uses `winsound` module)

##  How It Works
The script compares current system time with the user-defined alarm time. When both match, it triggers a sound alert.

##  Usage
```bash
python alarm.py